le="Pashai">Pashai</a>, <a href="/wiki/Hindki" title="Hindki">Hindki</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nuristani_people" title="Nuristani people">Nuristani</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brahui" title="Brahui">Brahui</a>, <a href="/wiki/Hindkowans" title="Hindkowans">Hindkowans</a>, etc.)</span></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Map_of_Languages_in_Afghanistan,_by_district.svg" class="image" title="Languages of Afghanistan (percentages are from CIA World Factbook)[1]  &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;50% Dari (Eastern Persian)   &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;35% Pashto       &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;8% Uzbek       &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;3% Turkmen         &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;4% Balochi &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;2% other (Nuristani, Pashai, Brahui, etc.)"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/Map_of_Languages_in_Afghanistan%2C_by_district.svg/180px-Map_of_Languages_in_Afghanistan%2C_by_district.svg.png" width="180" height="114" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
